I[Scroll]
C-f, C-b C-u, C-d scroll up/down by full/half page
zz scroll so that cursor is in the middle

[QuickFix]
]q [q go to next/prev in quickfix list
C-w <CR> open in new horizontal split

[Splits]
C-w L Move current split right
C-w H Move current split left
C-w <,> Move right window's edge left/right
C-w (C-)o Only keep this window


[Ctrl-P]
Run :CtrlP or :CtrlP [starting-directory] to invoke CtrlP in find file mode.
Run :CtrlPBuffer or :CtrlPMRU to start CtrlP in find buffer or find MRU file mode.
Run :CtrlPMixed to search in Files, Buffers and MRU files at the same time.

Press <c-f> and <c-b> to cycle between modes.
Press <c-d> to switch to filename search instead of full path.
Press <c-r> to switch to regexp mode.
Use <c-t> or <c-v>, <c-x> to open the selected entry in a new tab or in a new split.
Use <c-n>, <c-p> to select the next/previous string in the prompt's history.

Submit two or more dots .. to go up the directory tree by one or multiple levels.
End the input with a colon : followed by a command to execute it after opening the file:
Use :25 to jump to line 25.

[Search & highlight]
* Search for word under cursor
K Grep for word under cursor
C-] Go to definition
C-t Return (from C-])

[Show enters and spaces and stuff]
:set list
